                        "description": "<p>Lactobacillus&nbsp;johnsonii (Lj) was inoculated 1% (v/v) into fresh MRS medium or heat-killed Lj inoculated 1% (v/v) into fresh MRS medium, anaerobic, culture at 37 \u00b0C for 24 h, and then centrifuge (18,000 rpm, 4 \u00b0C for 20 min) to get supernatant, and store at -80 \u00b0C until analysis. N = 3 per group. Group ID: LJCS and MRS.</p><p><br></p><p>For cross-feeding assays, Bacteroides uniformis (BU) were grown overnight in BHI medium [supplemented with L-cysteine HCl (0.5 g/L), vitamin K1 (10 \u03bcL/L), hemin (5 mg/L) and resazurin (1 mg/L)] at 37 \u00b0C under anaerobic conditions, and 1% (v/v) of the BHI precultures was inoculated in the basal medium [proteose peptone, 10 g/L; beef extract, 10 g/L; yeast extract, 5 g/L; Tween 80, 1 ml/L; ammonium citrate trihydrate, 2 g/L; sodium acetate trihydrate, 5 g/L; magnesium sulfate, 0.1 g/L; manganese sulfate, 0.05 g/L; dipotassium phosphate, 2 g/L; L-cysteine HCl, 1 g/L and resazurin (1 mg/L)] containing \u03b2-glucan (BG) (5 g/L) or glucose (5 g/L) as the sole carbon source, respectively. Lj was grown overnight in MRS medium supplemented with L-cysteine HCl (0.5 g/L) at 37 \u00b0C under anaerobic conditions, and 1% (v/v) of the MRS precultures was inoculated in basal medium containing BG (5 g/L) or glucose (5 g/L) as the sole carbon source, respectively. N = 3 per group. Group ID: BU_0h, BU_48h and BU_48h_LJ24h.</p><p><br></p><p>For the \u03b2-glucan (BG) efficiency assay in colitic mice, mice were treated with 400 mg/kg of BG by daily gavage for 14 days, and 3% (w/v) dextran sulfate sodium salt (DSS) was added to the drinking water from day 7 to day 14. The DSS group was given an equivalent volume of PBS by gavage. The colon contents of mice were collected on day 14. N = 6 mice per group. Group ID: BG+DSS and DSS.</p><p><br></p><p>For the Lj efficiency assay in colitic mice, mice were treated with 1 x 10^8 CFU of Lj in 100 \u03bcL of sterile anaerobic PBS by daily gavage for 14 days, and 3% (w/v) DSS was added to the drinking water from day 7 to day 14. The vehicle group was given an equivalent volume of sterile anaerobic PBS by gavage. The colon contents of mice were collected on day 14. N = 6 mice per group. Group ID: Lj and Vehicle.</p>",
